Class OWLOntologyFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLOntologyFormat
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DLSyntaxHTMLOntologyFormat, DLSyntaxOntologyFormat, KRSS2OntologyFormat, KRSSOntologyFormat, LatexAxiomsListOntologyFormat, LatexOntologyFormat, OBOOntologyFormat, PrefixOWLOntologyFormat

    public abstract class OWLOntologyFormat
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Represents the concrete representation format of an ontology. The equality of an ontology format is defined by the equals and hashCode method (not its identity).
    Author:
    Matthew Horridge, The University Of Manchester, Bio-Health Informatics Group, Date: 02-Jan-2007
    See Also:

      • getOntologyLoaderMetaData

        public OWLOntologyLoaderMetaData getOntologyLoaderMetaData()
        If this format describes an ontology that was loaded from some ontology document (rather than created programmatically) there may be some meta data about the loading process. Subclasses of OWLOntologyFormat will provide accessors etc. to details pertaining to the meta data about loading.
        Returns:
        An object containing the meta data about loading. Not null.
